§14 We pass next to the brief narrative of the deaths of Vibius Cappadox and Balbutius‚ the latter of which was said to have taken place at the wedding-breakfast of Oppianicus the younger. Accius had adduced certain instances of violent conduct and rapacity, said to have been exhibited by Cluentius at various times ; this was the probabile ex vita, which was to prepare the minds of his hearers for the charges which he hoped to prove.
